/**

\page SerializationStructCompilerSample The MessageCompiler Sample

\section SerializationStructCompilerSampleSec The MessageCompiler Sample

The MessageCompiler utility converts \ref KristalliXMLSec "kNet Message XML Description Files" into C++ header files. These headers contain structures that implement the \ref SerializableMessageDoc "SerializableMessage" interface, which allows them to be passed to the \ref MessageConnection::Send function. This is the basis of declarative-mode data serialization in the kNet reference library.

The utility is invoked from the command line using the following syntax:

<div style="border: solid 1px black; background-color: #C0C0C0">
<pre style="padding-left: 5px; padding-top: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; border: 0px;">MessageCompiler <messagexmlfile>
</pre>
</div>

The tool outputs a .h file for each message found in the xml. For an example output, see \ref MsgPaintPixelExampleCode "MsgPaintPixel.h".

*/



